he glass into the shape of the mold. Cylindrical, conical and spherical shapes are possible utilizing the press bending process. Cylindrically bent parts are made when hot glass moves through Kevlar covered wheels that are driven by flexible shafts that bend or form the glass into a cylinder. Cylindrical glass parts are typically used in door glass applications.  \n</div>\n\n</div>','Capabilities','','inherit','open','open','','31-autosave','','','2013-05-01 19:36:52','2013-05-01 19:36:52','',31,'http://local.customglass/?p=33',0,'revision','',0),
