	(569,1,'2013-04-29 20:28:23','2013-04-29 20:28:23','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Construction & Agriculture</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\nConstruction equipment like bulldozers, skid-steers and cranes often work in harsh environments and must meet demanding standards. That’s why durable windshields, laminated glass and door glass are so essential in this segment. Guardian Custom Glass Solutions laminated glass systems play an important role in managing NVH properties and enhancing operator safety and comfort. \r\n\r\nAgricultural equipment is designed to maximize output and field performance while providing comfort during a hard day\'s work. Combine harvesters, row crop tractors, forestry equipment and more are constantly exposed to the elements, spending more days in the field and less time in the barn. Guardian provides infrared reflective glass, solar management glass, heated glass and privacy glass to help combat Mother Nature’s bad side.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;width:100%;overflow:auto;padding-top:20px\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/agriculture.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Forestry_body-copy-Image_344x152.jpg\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Construction and Agriculture','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-21','','','2013-04-29 20:28:23','2013-04-29 20:28:23','',11,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/11-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),
	(570,1,'2013-04-29 18:01:23','2013-04-29 18:01:23','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Capabilities</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Advanced Engineering Support</h2>\r\nWhen companies invest in sophisticated glass systems they require world class engineers and support staff that manage the process and help overcome design challenges. The Custom Glass Solutions team provides CAD/CAE support from conception to production. Predictive optical simulation tools provide the ability to analyze, diagnose and solve a complex engineering problem in one visit. The 3D scanner also helps more accurately diagnose current design issues. \r\n\r\nIn most cases, Custom Glass Solutions designs, fabricates and validates all tooling in-house, saving our customers time and money. Our full in-house testing capabilities ensure all products meet stringent safety and quality regulations as well as specific customer requirements.\r\n\r\nGlass is no longer just something you see through. Increasingly, glass is a complex, high-tech system that heightens your view, enhances your safety, improves your comfort level and more. Guardian has been fabricating glass for vehicles for more than 80 years, let us put our expertise to work for you.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Laminating</h2>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Laminating_344x152.jpg\" alt=\"Laminating\" />With more than 500,000 square feet of manufacturing space split between two facilities, Custom Glass Solutions is North America’s leading producer of large format, laminated glass. We produce pattern shapes in varying sizes and can include ceramic frit (paint), ground edges, holes, encapsulation and bonded hardware. We provide laminated glass solutions that block harmful UV rays, dampen exterior noise, quickly defog or deice, add protection, put <a href=\"/advanced-technologies/\">your name in lights</a> and more.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Tempering</h2>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tempering_344x152.jpg\" alt=\"Tempering\" style=\"padding-bottom: 60px;\" />Tempered glass, often referred to as safety glass, possesses increased strength and impact resistance compared to raw glass. The rapid heating and cooling of the glass deliberately adds stress to the glass, by placing the exterior of the surface in compression and the inner core of the glass in tension. This stress increases the surface compression of tempered glass and makes it harder to break. When tempered glass does break, its increased stress causes it to break into many small, dull pieces to help prevent injury.\r\n\r\nGuardian Custom Glass Solutions tempering furnaces produce tempered glass products such as door glass, roof glass, insulating glass, privacy glass and more. \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Bending</h2>\r\nCustom Glass Solutions bends glass utilizing three different capabilities – sag bending, press bending and cylindrical bending. Sag bent glass products are formed when hot glass sags (due to the pull of gravity) in to the shape of a quench ring. Sag bending produces barrel or spherical shaped glass parts. Press bent glass products utilize a stainless steel mold face and head that presses the glass into the shape of the mold. Cylindrical, conical and spherical shapes are possible utilizing the press bending process. Cylindrically bent parts are made when hot glass moves through Kevlar covered wheels that are driven by flexible shafts that bend or form the glass into a cylinder. Cylindrical glass parts are typically used in door glass applications.  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Capabilities','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-16','','','2013-04-29 18:01:23','2013-04-29 18:01:23','',31,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/31-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),
	(571,1,'2013-04-29 13:46:53','2013-04-29 13:46:53','<div class=\"products-container\">\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Windshields</h1>\r\n<h3>The Clear Choice is Custom Glass Solutions by Guardian</h3>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/driver.jpg\" />Custom Glass Solutions is the leading producer of large format, laminated glass in North America. Our sweeping one-piece windshields add safety, style and sophistication to RVs, buses, boats, trucks, trains, tractors and more. But size isn’t everything – we also offer advanced technologies in our windshields like infrared reflective coatings that keeps unwanted heat out; acoustic glass to help mitigate NVH effects; heated glass for efficient defrosting/deicing and more.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Door Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Door Glass Subhead</h3>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Product_Sunroof.jpg\" />In addition to windshields, Custom Glass Solutions specializes in door and roof glass systems. Whether it’s a photovoltaic, glass roof on an RV or tempered safety glass for school bus doors, Guardian will help you get it done.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Insulating Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Insulating Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nInsulating Glass (or glazing) is comprised of two panes of glass separated by an air or other gas filled space to reduce heat transfer. Typically used in school buses, Insulating Glass helps keep heat in during the winter and out during the summer. Insulating Glass is also used for its acoustic attenuation properties. The air or gas filled void improves the noise insulation quality and improves acoustical performance by reducing exterior noise transmission. Custom Glass Solutions has provided Insulating Glass as a “mid lite” (Insulating Glass Unit that is between the driver and the engine) for a number of niche, rear engine sports cars.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Solar Management Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Solar Subhead</h3>\r\nControlling the heat from the sun is no easy task, but Guardian is a leader in solar management glass solutions that:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create a more comfortable cabin</li>\r\n	<li>Increase fuel efficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce emissions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGuardian Solar Management Glass (SMG) absorbs, reflects or blocks the sun\'s rays while offering superior aesthetics and styling options thanks, in part, to our complex bending capabilities. Our SMG reduces solar load by absorbing a larger portion of the sun\'s heat compared to standard green glass. This industry-leading technology combines maximum solar heat absorbing capabilities for applications requiring over 70% visible light transmission with standard green glass aesthetics. Formulations are available for laminated, as well as monolithic systems.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Privacy Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Privacy Glass Subhead</h3>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Product_Switchable-Glass_344x152.jpg\" />When you’re looking to reduce thermal load, increase privacy and enhance styling options, ask Guardian Custom Glass Solutions about privacy glass. Typically known as “tinted” glass, Guardian’s privacy glass solutions are used in glazing areas that do not have a visible light transmission requirement. Our <b>PrivaGuard</b> and <b>MidNite Gray</b> glasses exhibit outstanding heat absorbing ability with deep-tinted, neutral gray aesthetics. Being formulation based, these products are ideal in applications where high solar performance uncoated glass is required. <b>PrivaGuard</b> and <b>MidNite Gray</b> are heat treatable in monolithic applications and do not require films or coatings to meet performance requirements.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Acoustic Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Acoustic Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nAcoustic Glass typically refers to laminated glass that often utilizes a special sound absorbing PVB interlayer. In addition to absorbing the noise within the glass, Acoustic Glass also reflects noise back toward the source. In ideal circumstances, Acoustic Glass can reduce total noise by as much as 10 decibels, which means a quieter, more comfortable ride for all.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Infrared Reflective Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Infrafred Reflective Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nGuardian’s infrared reflective glass, IRR, improves fuel efficiency by keeping unwanted heat out. Guardian IRR is a family of nano-particle thin film coated laminates that provide the highest available levels of solar energy reflection while selectively transmitting visible light. By reflecting the sun’s heat, these products achieve heat load reduction far superior to that of solar absorbing glass.\r\n\r\nThe coatings can be combined with a variety of glass substrates to achieve the full range - from maximum visible transmission and solar reflectivity to privacy-type light transmission combining solar reflectivity with absorbing solutions to achieve extremely low transmission levels.\r\n<div class=\"product-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/conventional.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/silverguard.jpg\" /></div>\r\n(IRR windshield absorbs ~3% of solar energy)\r\n\r\n<i>Studies done by the National Renewable Energy Laboratory (NREL) show that if every passenger vehicle in the United States converted to an IRR windshield, up to 10 gallons of fuel per vehicle could be saved annually or roughly 2.3 billion gallons nationwide.</i>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Anti-Reflective Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Anti-Reflective Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nGuardian’s anti-reflective (AR) glass has a durable, multilayer, sputtered anti-reflective coating applied to our own high quality float glass. The product is economical and highly effective at reducing reflectance and enhancing transmission – a combination that enables designers and engineers to achieve optimal performance.\r\n\r\nGuardian creates the AR product by vacuum depositing a multilayer anti-reflective coating developed at our Science and Technology Center onto our own high quality float glass. As the characteristics of the glass substrate are critical to overall performance, the glass itself is stringently specified and selected to ensure overall quality meets specifications desired by our customers. Automated in-line optical inspection throughout the float glass manufacturing and coating processes ensures quality, uniformity and consistency of final product.\r\n\r\nGuardian AR glass is offered with a single sided coating standard and is available with a double sided coating on request. The product is offered on glass substrates up to 96” by 144” and available in high volumes.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>DiamondGuard Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>DiamondGuard Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nGuardian’s DiamondGuard glass is fused with carbon strength through a patented process creating a protective coating that resists scratching, making it ideal for applications that require diamond-like toughness and lasting value. DiamondGuard scratch resistant glass lets you permanently protect your designs from the wear and tear of life’s everyday scuffs and scrapes without sacrificing clarity.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Products','','inherit','open','open','','16-revision-20','','','2013-04-29 13:46:53','2013-04-29 13:46:53','',16,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/16-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),
	(572,1,'2013-04-29 19:58:51','2013-04-29 19:58:51','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Commercial Transportation</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\" style=\"margin-top:20px;\">\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Commercial-Transportation_Truck_344x152.jpg\" style=\"padding-bottom:100px;\" />The commercial transportation segment includes Class 4 through 8 trucks, yard and short haul trucks and commercial shipping vessels. Guardian Custom Glass Solutions serves this diverse segment with glass <a href=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/products/\" title=\"Products\">products</a> and assemblies including windshields, door glass, sleeper cab units, heated glass, acoustic glass and privacy glass. We also provide coated glass solutions like infrared reflective and anti-reflective glass. <a href=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/advanced-technologies/\" title=\"Advanced Technologies\">Photovoltaic roof glass</a> can be employed on the top of trucks and trailers to offset fuel loss due to overnight idling. Guardian\'s infrared reflective coatings and lamination technologies eliminate more than 99% of all UV rays, protecting occupational drivers from skin damaging rays.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Commercial Transportation','','inherit','open','open','','39-revision-16','','','2013-04-29 19:58:51','2013-04-29 19:58:51','',39,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/39-revision-16/',0,'revision','',0),
	(573,1,'2013-04-29 20:15:11','2013-04-29 20:15:11','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Public Transportation</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Public-Transit_City-Bus.jpg\" style=\"padding-bottom:100px\" />Whether it’s school buses, mass transit buses or trains/trams/subways, Custom Glass Solutions provides glass systems that enhance safety and creature comforts. In fact, around 90% of North American school buses are equipped with Guardian glass, including insulating and privacy glass units. We also supply windshields, door glass, heated glass, scratch resistant coatings and films, anti-spall glass and more to public transportation customers. Our infrared reflective glass helps keep climate control more manageable, which makes for a more comfortable ride for drivers and passengers. Our embedded LED technology is the ideal solution for integrated marker lighting, improved pedestrian visibility and signage on buses and trains/trams/subways. \r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;width:100%;overflow:auto;padding-top:12px;\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Public-Transit_Train.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Public-Transit_School-Bus.jpg\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Public Transportation','','inherit','open','open','','44-revision-19','','','2013-04-29 20:15:11','2013-04-29 20:15:11','',44,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/44-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),
	(574,1,'2013-04-29 20:07:56','2013-04-29 20:07:56','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Lifestyle Vehicles</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\" style=\"margin-top:20px;\">\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Lifestyle-Vehicles_Motorhome.jpg\" style=\"padding-bottom:100px;\" />Whether your application requires robust solutions for a utilitarian purpose or <a href=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/advanced-technologies/\" title=\"Advanced Technologies\">advanced glass technologies</a> for absolute luxury, Guardian has a custom application for you. Large Class A RVs, towables, recreational marine vessels and enthusiast vehicles are designed for those who like to be on the open road (or sea) and demand the most from their vehicles. Guardian serves customers in this segment with large, one-piece windshields, tempered glass, solar management glass and laminated door/roof glass. Advanced glass technologies like photovoltaic roof glass and switchable glass are available for lifestyle vehicles.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Lifestyle Vehicles','','inherit','open','open','','48-revision-10','','','2013-04-29 20:07:56','2013-04-29 20:07:56','',48,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/48-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),
	(575,1,'2013-04-29 20:39:19','2013-04-29 20:39:19','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Construction & Agriculture</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\nConstruction equipment like bulldozers, skid-steers and cranes often work in harsh environments and must meet demanding standards. That’s why durable windshields, laminated glass and door glass are so essential in this segment. Guardian Custom Glass Solutions laminated glass systems play an important role in managing NVH properties and enhancing operator safety and comfort. \r\n\r\nAgricultural equipment is designed to maximize output and field performance while providing comfort during a hard day\'s work. Combine harvesters, row crop tractors, forestry equipment and more are constantly exposed to the elements, spending more days in the field and less time in the barn. Guardian provides infrared reflective glass, solar management glass, heated glass and privacy glass to help combat Mother Nature’s bad side.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;width:100%;overflow:auto;padding-top:20px\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/agriculture.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Forestry_body-copy-Image_344x152.jpg\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Construction and Agriculture','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-22','','','2013-04-29 20:39:19','2013-04-29 20:39:19','',11,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/11-revision-22/',0,'revision','',0),
	(576,1,'2013-04-29 20:16:59','2013-04-29 20:16:59','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Safety & Protection</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"EMS\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Safety-and-Protection_Ambulance.jpg\" />Guardian glass provides superior durability and OEM fit and finish for police, fire, rescue and recovery vehicles. Our laminated and tempered glass systems play an important role in these vehicles. Custom Glass Solutions also provides heated glass and privacy glass and we recently introduced a fire truck windshield that includes embedded LEDs to help identify the vehicle day or night, rain or shine. We proudly support our United States Fire, Police and service professionals with American made glass products. When durability and dependability are a must, make sure you’ve got Guardian glass.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;width:100%;overflow:auto;padding-top:30px;\">\r\n<img alt=\"Police\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Safety-and-Protection_Police.jpg\" /><img alt=\"Fire Truck\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Safety-and-Protection_Fire-Truck.jpg\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Safety and Protection','','inherit','open','open','','50-revision-11','','','2013-04-29 20:16:59','2013-04-29 20:16:59','',50,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/50-revision-11/',0,'revision','',0),
	(577,1,'2013-04-29 20:11:55','2013-04-29 20:11:55','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Non-Mobility</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Non-Mobility_Washer.jpg\" style=\"padding-bottom:100px;\" />Even if it doesn’t move your application may still require or desire a custom, sophisticated glass system. Take washers and dryers as an example where Custom Glass Solutions’ advanced tempering, bending and encapsulating <a href=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/capabilities/\" title=\"Capabilities\">capabilities</a> enable us to provide the ideal solution for appliances that demand performance and aesthetics. Or coin operated machines, where our anti-reflective glass, DiamondGuard scratch resistant glass and low maintenance glass provide added value and enhance the user experience. And, Guardian has been providing glass solutions for the solar industry from its infancy, including concentrated solar power and secondary reflective mirroring. Our low-iron glass and UltraMirror products help improve efficiencies in solar cells and mirrors for high performance applications. \r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;width:100%;overflow:auto;padding-top:30px;\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Non-Mobility_Slot-Machine.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/PinBall_344x152.jpg\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Non-Mobility','','inherit','open','open','','52-revision-12','','','2013-04-29 20:11:55','2013-04-29 20:11:55','',52,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/52-revision-12/',0,'revision','',0),
	(578,1,'2013-04-29 15:57:06','2013-04-29 15:57:06','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Advanced Technologies</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Embedded LEDs</h2>\r\n\r\nGuardian’s patented process for embedding LEDs in laminated glass gives customers a myriad of styling options. Whether it’s prominently displaying a brand name in lights or replacing traditional exterior turn signals and brake lights, Guardian’s embedded LED solution takes sophistication and styling to a whole new level. \r\n\r\n<div style=\"clear:both;width:100%;overflow:auto;margin:20px 0 20px 0;\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Fire-Truck-LEDs_1.jpg\" style=\"float:left;\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Fire-Truck-LEDs_2.jpg\" style=\"float:right;\" />\r\n</div>\r\n\r\nCompanies no longer have to rely on decals that are susceptible to wear and tear from exposure to the elements. Instead, brand names, makes, models and more can be displayed in lights that are permanently protected by Guardian glass.\r\n\r\nGuardian’s embedded LEDs are also perfect for exterior indicators including turn signals, brake lights, flashers and more. We’ve even developed methods for diffusing the light from the LEDs, which creates applications for interior, ambient lighting.\r\n\r\nLEDs are available in multiple colors and circuits can be designed to run on multiple DC voltages to meet customer requirements.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Photovoltaic Roof Glass</h2>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Product_Sunroof.jpg\" />The concept is simple: collect energy from the sun and convert it to usable power for a vehicle. The execution however, is best left to the glass experts at Custom Glass Solutions. From the Toyota Prius to the Fisker Karma, photovoltaic (PV) roof glass is becoming more prevalent in the automotive industry. Guardian Custom Glass Solutions is taking similar technology and adapting it for use in vehicles with substantial real estate available for PV cells like recreational vehicles, heavy trucks, trains, buses, ships and more.\r\n\r\nGuardian’s PV roof glass solution utilizes low-iron, laminated glass to protect the PV cells from the elements and expose the cells to as much sunlight as possible. We are able to customize size, shape and artwork to seamlessly integrate PV roof glass into customer designs. Ask us how PV roof glass could power your application.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Switchable Glass</h2>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Product_Switchable-Glass_344x152.jpg\" />Guardian’s Switchable Glass transitions from opaque to transparent with the flick of a switch. This high-tech privacy glass solution uses a low-voltage electrical current to arrange liquid crystal molecules into a pattern that makes glass transparent when turned on. Turned off, the liquid crystal molecules revert to a random pattern, diffusing the light and causing the glass to become opaque.\r\n\r\nCustom Glass Solutions is offering switchable glass in various applications for recreational vehicles, ships, limousines and more. \r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Advanced Technologies','','inherit','open','open','','35-revision-18','','','2013-04-29 15:57:06','2013-04-29 15:57:06','',35,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/35-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),
	(579,1,'2013-04-25 05:29:18','2013-04-25 05:29:18','<div class=\"text-container\">\r\n<h1>About</h1>\r\n<p>Guardian’s Custom Glass Solutions group was formed to meet the glass needs of diverse transportation segments such as <a href=\"/commercial-transportation/\" title=\"Commercial Transportation\">commercial</a> & <a href=\"/public-transit/\" title=\"Public Transportation\">public transportation</a>, <a href=\"/construction-and-agriculture/\" title=\"Construction and Agriculture\">construction & agriculture</a>, <a href=\"/safety-and-protection/\" title=\"Safety and Protection\">safety & protection</a>, <a href=\"/lifestyle-vehicles/\" title=\"Lifestyle Vehicles\">lifestyle vehicles</a> and more. Headquartered in Ohio, Custom Glass Solutions manages volumes ranging from 10 parts to 100,000 parts per year, all to serve a diverse set of customers. The group manufactures flat, bent, laminated and tempered glass systems with a dedicated footprint to custom manufacturing. Utilizing the resources of its parent company, <a href=\"http://guardian.com/\" title=\"Guardian Industries\">Guardian Industries</a>, Custom Glass Solutions offers everything from research & development to technical and marketing support required of advanced glass solutions. With full in-house testing capabilities, Custom Glass Solutions ensures all products meet stringent safety and quality regulations as well as specific customer requirements.</p>\r\n<p>Whether it’s small and flat, large and bent or something in between, Guardian has a custom glass solution for you. When you have an idea that involves glass, we have the engineering capabilities to make it a reality. Contact us to learn more.</p>\r\n<p>Check out our latest <a href=\"/category/news/\" title=\"News\">news</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Learn more about <a href=\"http://guardian.com/\" title=\"Guardian Industries\">Guardian</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','About','','inherit','open','open','','405-revision-3','','','2013-04-25 05:29:18','2013-04-25 05:29:18','',405,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/405-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),
	(580,1,'2013-04-29 21:15:03','2013-04-29 21:15:03','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Capabilities</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Advanced Engineering Support</h2>\r\nWhen companies invest in sophisticated glass systems they require world class engineers and support staff that manage the process and help overcome design challenges. The Custom Glass Solutions team provides CAD/CAE support from conception to production. Predictive optical simulation tools provide the ability to analyze, diagnose and solve a complex engineering problem in one visit. The 3D scanner also helps more accurately diagnose current design issues. \r\n\r\nIn most cases, Custom Glass Solutions designs, fabricates and validates all tooling in-house, saving our customers time and money. Our full in-house testing capabilities ensure all products meet stringent safety and quality regulations as well as specific customer requirements.\r\n\r\nGlass is no longer just something you see through. Increasingly, glass is a complex, high-tech system that heightens your view, enhances your safety, improves your comfort level and more. Guardian has been fabricating glass for vehicles for more than 80 years, let us put our expertise to work for you.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Laminating</h2>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Laminating_344x152.jpg\" alt=\"Laminating\" />With more than 500,000 square feet of manufacturing space split between two facilities, Custom Glass Solutions is North America’s leading producer of large format, laminated glass. We produce pattern shapes in varying sizes and can include ceramic frit (paint), ground edges, holes, encapsulation and bonded hardware. We provide laminated glass solutions that block harmful UV rays, dampen exterior noise, quickly defog or deice, add protection, put <a href=\"/advanced-technologies/\">your name in lights</a> and more.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Tempering</h2>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Tempering_344x152.jpg\" alt=\"Tempering\" style=\"padding-bottom: 60px;\" />Tempered glass, often referred to as safety glass, possesses increased strength and impact resistance compared to raw glass. The rapid heating and cooling of the glass deliberately adds stress to the glass, by placing the exterior of the surface in compression and the inner core of the glass in tension. This stress increases the surface compression of tempered glass and makes it harder to break. When tempered glass does break, its increased stress causes it to break into many small, dull pieces to help prevent injury.\r\n\r\nGuardian Custom Glass Solutions tempering furnaces produce tempered glass products such as door glass, roof glass, insulating glass, privacy glass and more. \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Bending</h2>\r\nCustom Glass Solutions bends glass utilizing three different capabilities – sag bending, press bending and cylindrical bending. Sag bent glass products are formed when hot glass sags (due to the pull of gravity) in to the shape of a quench ring. Sag bending produces barrel or spherical shaped glass parts. Press bent glass products utilize a stainless steel mold face and head that presses the glass into the shape of the mold. Cylindrical, conical and spherical shapes are possible utilizing the press bending process. Cylindrically bent parts are made when hot glass moves through Kevlar covered wheels that are driven by flexible shafts that bend or form the glass into a cylinder. Cylindrical glass parts are typically used in door glass applications.  \r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>','Capabilities','','inherit','open','open','','31-revision-17','','','2013-04-29 21:15:03','2013-04-29 21:15:03','',31,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/31-revision-17/',0,'revision','',0),
	(581,1,'2013-04-29 21:17:57','2013-04-29 21:17:57','<div class=\"products-container\">\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Windshields</h1>\r\n<h3>The Clear Choice is Custom Glass Solutions by Guardian</h3>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/driver.jpg\" />Custom Glass Solutions is the leading producer of large format, laminated glass in North America. Our sweeping one-piece windshields add safety, style and sophistication to RVs, buses, boats, trucks, trains, tractors and more. But size isn’t everything – we also offer advanced technologies in our windshields like infrared reflective coatings that keeps unwanted heat out; acoustic glass to help mitigate NVH effects; heated glass for efficient defrosting/deicing and more.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Door Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Door Glass Subhead</h3>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Product_Sunroof.jpg\" />In addition to windshields, Custom Glass Solutions specializes in door and roof glass systems. Whether it’s a photovoltaic, glass roof on an RV or tempered safety glass for school bus doors, Guardian will help you get it done.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Insulating Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Insulating Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nInsulating Glass (or glazing) is comprised of two panes of glass separated by an air or other gas filled space to reduce heat transfer. Typically used in school buses, Insulating Glass helps keep heat in during the winter and out during the summer. Insulating Glass is also used for its acoustic attenuation properties. The air or gas filled void improves the noise insulation quality and improves acoustical performance by reducing exterior noise transmission. Custom Glass Solutions has provided Insulating Glass as a “mid lite” (Insulating Glass Unit that is between the driver and the engine) for a number of niche, rear engine sports cars.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Solar Management Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Solar Subhead</h3>\r\nControlling the heat from the sun is no easy task, but Guardian is a leader in solar management glass solutions that:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Create a more comfortable cabin</li>\r\n	<li>Increase fuel efficiency</li>\r\n	<li>Reduce emissions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nGuardian Solar Management Glass (SMG) absorbs, reflects or blocks the sun\'s rays while offering superior aesthetics and styling options thanks, in part, to our complex bending capabilities. Our SMG reduces solar load by absorbing a larger portion of the sun\'s heat compared to standard green glass. This industry-leading technology combines maximum solar heat absorbing capabilities for applications requiring over 70% visible light transmission with standard green glass aesthetics. Formulations are available for laminated, as well as monolithic systems.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Privacy Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Privacy Glass Subhead</h3>\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Product_Switchable-Glass_344x152.jpg\" />When you’re looking to reduce thermal load, increase privacy and enhance styling options, ask Guardian Custom Glass Solutions about privacy glass. Typically known as “tinted” glass, Guardian’s privacy glass solutions are used in glazing areas that do not have a visible light transmission requirement. Our <b>PrivaGuard</b> and <b>MidNite Gray</b> glasses exhibit outstanding heat absorbing ability with deep-tinted, neutral gray aesthetics. Being formulation based, these products are ideal in applications where high solar performance uncoated glass is required. <b>PrivaGuard</b> and <b>MidNite Gray</b> are heat treatable in monolithic applications and do not require films or coatings to meet performance requirements.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Acoustic Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Acoustic Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nAcoustic Glass typically refers to laminated glass that often utilizes a special sound absorbing PVB interlayer. In addition to absorbing the noise within the glass, Acoustic Glass also reflects noise back toward the source. In ideal circumstances, Acoustic Glass can reduce total noise by as much as 10 decibels, which means a quieter, more comfortable ride for all.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Infrared Reflective Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Infrafred Reflective Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nGuardian’s infrared reflective glass, IRR, improves fuel efficiency by keeping unwanted heat out. Guardian IRR is a family of nano-particle thin film coated laminates that provide the highest available levels of solar energy reflection while selectively transmitting visible light. By reflecting the sun’s heat, these products achieve heat load reduction far superior to that of solar absorbing glass.\r\n\r\nThe coatings can be combined with a variety of glass substrates to achieve the full range - from maximum visible transmission and solar reflectivity to privacy-type light transmission combining solar reflectivity with absorbing solutions to achieve extremely low transmission levels.\r\n<div class=\"product-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/conventional.jpg\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/silverguard.jpg\" /></div>\r\n(IRR windshield absorbs ~3% of solar energy)\r\n\r\n<i>Studies done by the National Renewable Energy Laboratory (NREL) show that if every passenger vehicle in the United States converted to an IRR windshield, up to 10 gallons of fuel per vehicle could be saved annually or roughly 2.3 billion gallons nationwide.</i>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>Anti-Reflective Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>Anti-Reflective Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nGuardian’s anti-reflective (AR) glass has a durable, multilayer, sputtered anti-reflective coating applied to our own high quality float glass. The product is economical and highly effective at reducing reflectance and enhancing transmission – a combination that enables designers and engineers to achieve optimal performance.\r\n\r\nGuardian creates the AR product by vacuum depositing a multilayer anti-reflective coating developed at our Science and Technology Center onto our own high quality float glass. As the characteristics of the glass substrate are critical to overall performance, the glass itself is stringently specified and selected to ensure overall quality meets specifications desired by our customers. Automated in-line optical inspection throughout the float glass manufacturing and coating processes ensures quality, uniformity and consistency of final product.\r\n\r\nGuardian AR glass is offered with a single sided coating standard and is available with a double sided coating on request. The product is offered on glass substrates up to 96” by 144” and available in high volumes.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n<h1>DiamondGuard Glass</h1>\r\n<h3>DiamondGuard Glass Subhead</h3>\r\nGuardian’s DiamondGuard glass is fused with carbon strength through a patented process creating a protective coating that resists scratching, making it ideal for applications that require diamond-like toughness and lasting value. DiamondGuard scratch resistant glass lets you permanently protect your designs from the wear and tear of life’s everyday scuffs and scrapes without sacrificing clarity.\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Products','','inherit','open','open','','16-revision-21','','','2013-04-29 21:17:57','2013-04-29 21:17:57','',16,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/16-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),
	(582,1,'2013-04-29 23:39:03','2013-04-29 23:39:03','<div class=\"text-container\">\r\n<h1>About</h1>\r\n<p>Guardian’s Custom Glass Solutions group was formed to meet the glass needs of diverse transportation segments such as <a href=\"/commercial-transportation/\" title=\"Commercial Transportation\">commercial</a> & <a href=\"/public-transit/\" title=\"Public Transportation\">public transportation</a>, <a href=\"/construction-and-agriculture/\" title=\"Construction and Agriculture\">construction & agriculture</a>, <a href=\"/safety-and-protection/\" title=\"Safety and Protection\">safety & protection</a>, <a href=\"/lifestyle-vehicles/\" title=\"Lifestyle Vehicles\">lifestyle vehicles</a> and more. Headquartered in Ohio, Custom Glass Solutions manages volumes ranging from 10 parts to 100,000 parts per year, all to serve a diverse set of customers. The group manufactures flat, bent, laminated and tempered glass systems with a dedicated footprint to custom manufacturing. Utilizing the resources of its parent company, <a href=\"http://guardian.com/\" title=\"Guardian Industries\">Guardian Industries</a>, Custom Glass Solutions offers everything from research & development to technical and marketing support required of advanced glass solutions. With full in-house testing capabilities, Custom Glass Solutions ensures all products meet stringent safety and quality regulations as well as specific customer requirements.</p>\r\n<p>Whether it’s small and flat, large and bent or something in between, Guardian has a custom glass solution for you. When you have an idea that involves glass, we have the engineering capabilities to make it a reality. Contact us to learn more.</p>\r\n<p>Check out our latest <a href=\"/category/news/\" title=\"News\">news</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Learn more about <a href=\"http://guardian.com/\" title=\"Guardian Industries\">Guardian</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n</div>','About','','inherit','open','open','','405-revision-4','','','2013-04-29 23:39:03','2013-04-29 23:39:03','',405,'http://www.customglasssolutions.com/405-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),
	(583,1,'2013-04-30 00:19:31','2013-04-30 00:19:31','<div class=\"products-container\"><header id=\"page-header\">\r\n<h1>Capabilities</h1>\r\n</header>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Advanced Engineering Support</h2>\r\nWhen companies invest in sophisticated glass systems they require world class engineers and support staff that manage the process and help overcome design challenges. The Custom Glass Solutions team provides CAD/CAE support from conception to production. Predictive optical simulation tools provide the ability to analyze, diagnose and solve a complex engineering problem in one visit. The 3D scanner also helps more accurately diagnose current design issues. \r\n\r\nIn most cases, Custom Glass Solutions designs, fabricates and validates all tooling in-house, saving our customers time and money. Our full in-house testing capabilities ensure all products meet stringent safety and quality regulations as well as specific customer requirements.\r\n\r\nGlass is no longer just something you see through. Increasingly, glass is a complex, high-tech system that heightens your view, enhances your safety, improves your comfort level and more. Guardian has been fabricating glass for vehicles for more than 80 years, let us put our expertise to work for you.\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"product\">\r\n\r\n<h2>Laminating</h2>\r\n<img src=\"http://www.customglasssolutions.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/Laminating_344x152.jpg\" alt=\"Laminating\" />With more than 500,000 square feet of manufacturing space split between two facilities, Custom Glass Solutions is North America’s leading producer of large format, laminated glass. We produce pattern shapes in varying sizes and can include ceramic frit (paint), ground edges, holes, encapsulation and bonded hardware. We provide laminated glass solutions that block harmful UV rays, dampen exterior noise, quickly defog or deice, add protection, put <a href=\"/advanced-technologies/\">your name in lights</a> and more.\